        {"type": "bullets.show", "id": "short-frame-notes", "atMs": 700, "durationMs": 1900, "title": "Frameless codegen", "items": ["C locals become registers", "No heap-visible frame", "7.6x → 1.6x recursion"], "bounds": {"x": 0.07, "y": 0.59, "width": 0.86, "height": 0.34}},
        {"type": "focus.show", "id": "short-frame-focus", "target": "short-frame-code", "atMs": 3500, "relativeBounds": {"x": 0.03, "y": 0.08, "width": 0.94, "height": 0.30}, "label": "C locals, not tagged stack slots", "color": "50d8ff"}
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "short-bounds",
      "durationMs": 17000,
      "narration": {
        "text": "Second, a bounds failure used to return into the loop. That reachable call forced reloads on every pass. Making the failure path leave the method let clang hoist array metadata while preserving every check."
      },
      "actions": [
        {"type": "text.show", "id": "short-bounds-title", "atMs": 0, "text": "The check was not the problem", "uiid": "VideoTitle", "responsive": true, "maxLines": 2, "bounds": {"x": 0.08, "y": 0.02, "width": 0.84, "height": 0.10}},
        {"type": "code.show", "id": "short-bounds-code", "atMs": 0, "language": "c", "path": "hotspot-bounds.c.txt", "bounds": {"x": 0.05, "y": 0.13, "width": 0.90, "height": 0.43}},
        {"type": "transition", "target": "short-bounds-code", "atMs": 0, "durationMs": 500, "effect": "fade", "easing": "ease-out"},
        {"type": "bullets.show", "id": "short-bounds-notes", "atMs": 700, "durationMs": 1900, "title": "Control flow was the bug", "items": ["Failure now diverges", "Metadata leaves the loop", "Quicksort: 0.92x HotSpot"], "bounds": {"x": 0.07, "y": 0.59, "width": 0.86, "height": 0.34}},
        {"type": "focus.show", "id": "short-bounds-focus", "target": "short-bounds-code", "atMs": 3600, "relativeBounds": {"x": 0.03, "y": 0.43, "width": 0.94, "height": 0.33}, "label": "Throw, then leave the method", "color": "ffc857"}
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "short-memory",
      "durationMs": 17000,
      "narration": {
        "text": "Third, the BiBOP heap replaced one malloc and tracking search per object with page-local pointer bumps. Peak allocation churn fell below Java twenty five, while the idle floor stayed at two point four megabytes."
      },
      "actions": [
        {"type": "svg.show", "id": "short-memory-chart", "atMs": 100, "path": "hotspot-memory-portrait.svg", "bounds": {"x": 0.06, "y": 0.06, "width": 0.88, "height": 0.88}},
        {"type": "transition", "target": "short-memory-chart", "atMs": 100, "durationMs": 700, "effect": "morph", "easing": "ease-in-out"}
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "short-tagged",
      "durationMs": 17000,
      "narration": {
        "text": "Finally, boxed integers became tagged pointer values on sixty-four-bit targets. Boxing allocates nothing, but Integer identity changes, so the build rejects synchronization on primitive wrappers instead of hiding the tradeoff."
      },
